  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is a single blinded (Outcome Assessors), multicenter randomized controlled study
      designed to investigate if a silver alloyed urinary catheter with antibacterial properties
      can reduce the incidence of catheter acquired urinary tract infections in patients undergoing
      elective surgery. Patients requiring urinary catheterization will be randomized into two
      groups and receive either the silver alloyed catheter (test) or a silicone catheter
      (control).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
